27/03/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Leaders of the Alliance of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), the Social Democratic Party (SDP), the Croatian Democratic Union of BiH (HDZ BiH), and HDZ 1990 signed a declaration in Mostar on Friday (March 25th) on co-operation in efforts to overcome the crisis in forming a new central government.
They urged all political parties in parliament to join talks to resolve the issue.
Discussions with representatives of Bosniak parties will be held next week.
(RTRS, Dnevnik, Tanjug, Kurir, Nezavisne Novine - 25/03/11)
